coup cannot be played optimally by a machine learning model because it lacks the ability to encode historical information
about how other players have acted in previous turns. Without this context, the model cannot accurately calculate probabilities of players having different cards.

Therefore along side the public and private data, each model would be required to have access to the public estimation of the probabilities that each player had each card.
